INSIGHTS

In this section, we explore different theories and correlations found within Fantasy Premier League data.

Talisman Theory is the idea that in each team is a key individual (the Talisman) who will provide the most likely source of points, and should be selected as coverage for teams with favorable fixtures.

Price-points correlation measures the value of a player normalized for his expected point return given his price point.
